    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The cab for 5000
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                and 9000
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                Series premium conventional tractors and 9000
                <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                Series Pro Sleeper&#174; models is made of aluminum to resist corrosion and to reduce vehicle weight
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602101">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>. Riveted construction adds strength and improves
                repairability over the 100% welded cabs. Structural sealers increase joint strength.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1602101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g1602101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. 5000
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    and 9000
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    Series Conventional Cab
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The combination of riveted construction and adhesive sealers provides a much tighter fitting cab than
                conventional welded steel, and eliminates air leaks, reduces road noise and improves driver comfort.
            </para>
            <para>
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602102">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                shows day cab and Pro Sleeper&#174; cab models. The Pro Sleeper&#174; has two different cab sizes, the
                112 inch (51 inch sleeper) and the 120 inch (72 inch sleeper) BBC (bumper to back of cab). The Pro
                Sleeper&#174; also has three different roof designs: the Low Roof design, Hi-Rise design and the
                Sky-Rise design.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1602102" figsize="full-pg">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g1602102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="592px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. 5000
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    and 9000
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    Series Cabs
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
